title: Without Reserve: Schenker stretches out in Eastern Creek Business Park
text:
Schenker Australia (DB Schenker) is expanding its presence at the Eastern Creek Business Park.
Schenker Australia P/L, known as DB Schenker, is expanding its footprint within Frasers Property Australia's Eastern Creek Business Park with a 4.8 hectare site, comprising a 24,250-square-metre warehouse and a 250-square-metre office, over a 10-year period. That takes its total occupancy to 40,000 square metres within the estate. The total value of the facility expansion is about $65 million.
Walk for charity The property sector has been busy raising cash for charity. More than 1000 CBRE staff worked up a sweat on Friday as they took part in a 10-kilometre walk from Martin Place, through Double Bay and Rushcutters Bay and finishing at the North Bondi Surf Club. It's part of the firm's flagship charity event, Walk For A Wish, which has raised more than $1 million since its inception in 2009. Nine property professionals from JLL's Young Guns group also collectively raised more than $2000 for the Roughtober Sleepout on Friday night. The Roughtober Sleepout raises funds for the homeless support work provided by Rough Edges Cafe in Darlinghurst, Sydney.
